Page Image

Page Content​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​Since 2002, CITIC Capital has grown considerably and become a scalable and internationally recognized investment management firm with a comprehensive China focused investment platform.​ ​2002​Incorporation of CITIC Capital Markets Holdings Limited​ 2003​Launch 1st hedge fund - CITIC Capital China Plus Fund​​Launch 1st US buyout fund - CITIC Equity Partners, L.P.​​​Open Shanghai and Tokyo office​ 2004​​Launch 1st Japan buyout fund - CITIC Japan Partners, L.P.​​​Open Beijing office​​ 2005​Launch 1st real estate fund - CITIC Capital China Property Fund, L.P.​​​Launch 1st mezzanine fund​​ - CITIC Capital China Mezzanine Fund Limited​​​Open New York office​ 2006​​Launch 2nd real estate fund co-invested with China Vanke Co., Ltd​ - CITIC Capital Vanke China Property Development Fund, L.P.​​​​Rename CITIC Capital Markets Holdings Limited as CITIC Capital Holdings Limited (“CCHL”). Announce new organization structure with investment management as focus​​Launch 1st China buyout fund - CITIC Capital China Partners, L.P.​​ 2007​Launch 2nd US buyout fund - CITIC Equity Partners II, L.P.​​Launch 3rd real estate fund - CITIC Capital China Real Estate Investment Fund III, L.P.​ 2008​Launch 1st venture fund - Kaixin Investment Co., Ltd (Joint venture with China Development Bank)​ 2009​Launch 2nd China buyout fund - CITIC Capital China Partners II, L.P.​ 2010​Launch 2nd Japan buyout fund - CITIC Capital Japan Partners II, L.P.​​​Launch CITIC Kazyna Investment Fund I, a JV with a subsidiary of the sovereign wealth fund "Samruk-Kazyna" of the Republic of Kazakhstan​ 2011​Launch 3rd US/International buyout fund - CITIC Capital International Partners III, L.P.​​​Launch 2nd mezzanine fund - CITIC Capital China Opportunities, L.P.​​​Launch 4th real estate fund - CITIC Capital China Retail Properties Investment Fund, L.P.​​​Launch 1st RMB Multi-Asset Class Fund ​​ 2012​Launch 2nd venture fund - CITIC Capital Venture Partners, L.P.​ 2014​Establish CCTrack Solutions, a new multi-strategy hedge fund platform targeting institutional investors in North America, Europe, and the Asian markets​​Launch 3rd venture fund (an RMB product) - CITIC Capital (Shenzhen) Incubator Fund​Set up China Asset Management, a new investment platform focusing on Greater China onshore, offshore, and cross-border investment products ​through QDII, RQDII, QFII and RQFII channels​​ 2015​​Ope​n Shenzhen office for the management and distribution of RMB investment products​ 2016​Launch 5th real estate fund - CITIC Capital London Property Fund, L.P.​​​Launch CITIC Capital Silk Road Fund 2017​Form strategic partnership with Stockbridge Capital Group LLC, a fully independent real estate investment management firm with assets spanning all major real estate property types in the US​​​Launch 3rd Japan buyout fund - CITIC Capital Japan Partners III, L.P.​​
















































































